<section class="oe_container">
   <div class="oe_row oe_spaced">
           <h2 class="oe_slogan" style="color:olive;"><b>Attachment/Document Extension with Directory and Numbering Security & Tags</h2>
       <p class="oe_mt32" style="color:olive;">
This module will add below features to document/attachment module of Odoo.</p>


<p style="color:red;">
Document Manager can do below listed features.</p><p style="color:blue;">
1. Creation directory/folder by model/object. Document manager can see all directories and attachment without any restriction.<br/>
2. Every directory/folder having separate sequence numbering for attachments.<br/>
3. Security on directory so only specific group can access/create document/attachment inside that directory. (Optional if you do not select group then no security).<br/>
4. Directory view.<br/>
7. If there is not directory available for any model/object then attachment/document will follow DOC/ generic sequence.<br/>
8. Can create/add/select Document Tags<br/>
9. Can create/add/select Directory Tags<br/>
       </p>

<p style="color:red;">
Document User can do below listed features.</p><p style="color:blue;">
1. View directory/folder by model/object. Document User can see only directories where he/she assigned as users on that directory form by Document Manager<br/>
2. Every directory/folder having separate sequence numbering for attachments.<br/>
3. Security on directory so only specific group can access/create document/attachment inside that directory. (Optional if you do not select group then no security).<br/>
4. Directory view.<br/>
7. If there is not directory available for any model/object then attachment/document will follow DOC/ generic sequence.<br/>
8. Can select Document Tags<br/>
9. Can select Directory Tags<br/>
       </p>

<p style="color:red;">
Employee can do below listed features.</p><p style="color:blue;">
1. Employee can only see this menu Document/My Documents/My Documents and once employee click it will list only document where employee is owner. Other attachment will be hidden for him/her.<br/>
       </p>
 
       <p><p style="color:green">Available Menus:</p>
            <ul style="color:blue;">
              <li>Document</li>
              <li>--Document/Directories</li>
              <li>----Document/Directories/Directories</li>
              <li>----Document/Directories/Directories Structure</li>
              <li>--Document/All Documents</li>
              <li>----Document/All Documents/All Documents</li>
              <li>--Document/Configuration</li>
              <li>----Document/Configuration/Directory Tags</li>
              <li>----Document/Configuration/Document Tags</li>
              <li>--Document/My Documents</li>
              <li>----Document/My Documents/My Documents</li>
            </ul>
         </p>
   </div>
</section>
